			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Druid, shaman, or cleric for plvl<a name="26353"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 9 04 9:30 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have PL'd a cleric up to 64, a druid up to 52, and I'm working on a shammie (51 atm, and pausing to get aa). 
<br />

<br />
I mainly use the druid as a port bot.  The cleric is great for buffing, but I'm thinking it may be better to just toss a virtue on me and then go with the shammie...
<br />

<br />
Oh wait, you want the other way around.  ;)
<br />

<br />
Up to level 30 a druid is your best friend (actually past 30, but 30 is about when it slows down, but it's still quite doable).  
<br />

<br />
Everyone complains about low offense/defense.  Well, if you want to waste a lot of time and not get exp, then just keep the DS on at all times.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
What you want to do is keep skin on at all times, a str buff, and regen.  To start, use DS and go straight up to level 10.  You can do this most anywhere. 
<br />

<br />
Spend your practices to get at least a few points in skills.  Then go somewhere and be prepared to spend an hour or so whiffing at 2-3 somethings while you work your offense/defense/one weapon skill up.  After a while, your defense will be capped, and your melee skills will be enough that you'll usually hit most things about your level once so you can start doing the DS again.  I recommend yard trash in unrest.  Get 2-4 beetles and you are good. 
<br />

<br />
Do the DS thing again and go to about 17.  Get all your new skills trained, then do the same thing you did at 10.    Only now you can dual wield.  So get a pair of fast weapons (it doesn't matter if they have lame damage, just make sure they are fast) of each type, and go sit somewhere with 2-3 blues on you and swing swing swing.  Your weapon skills and defense will get capped in a short time.  You can do this with yard trash in unrest still, only you'll probably need the undead rather than beetles.  Alternately, you can use the lizard thingys in paludal (by the hollowshade moor zone at the pool). 
<br />

<br />
Now that you've got your skills up, it shouldn't be a problem to keep your weapon skill topped off each level.  You'll probably spend about 1/3 of the level getting your skills up, then DS to finish the level and repeat.  Exp slows down a bit, so you shouldn't have issues getting this fairly quick.  Start around 17 or so you can go in the house in unrest, or keep killing stuff in paludal.  
<br />

<br />
Once you hit 30, go find a quiet spot and practice your instrument skills, since they all suck at this point. :p
<br />

<br />
At about 35 I tend to group with a 52 alt and let the higher level kill stuff to get exp faster, then at 43 they can group with my bard for swarm kiting or AE.  Since you are PL'ing a bard, once you get your second DoT, you can effectively PL yourself and not worry about it.  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
