				<td colspan="2"><span>A Shaman is a great PLer for various reasons, buffs, regen, slows and heals. Druids are just as good minus the slows and a few buffs. If you can have both together then you’re talking  some serious PLing.
<br />

<br />
My friend and I have a 2nd account. We made it as a utility group, we’ve PLed our primary characters, Druid (ports), Mage (summoned items/focus), Shaman (buffs), Cleric (reses) and Enchanter (head buffs) into their high 20’s and 30’s, the Cleric is 40 now and going strong. Most of it was done with my 65 Druid and we buffed them with my 40 Shaman. 
<br />

<br />
The down side is that we wanted our skills to be maxed, so we had to spend hours upon hours getting their spell skills up, but they are all maxed now and it was well worth it. Took us a total of 8 weeks to get them where we wanted them. It was a lot of fun. 
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
