				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Druid, shaman, or cleric for plvl<a name="26630"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 10 04 8:46 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hmmm.... I didn't know bards needed PLing, LOL.
<br />

<br />
The only PLing I did was from mid 30ish to mid 40ish. I went to Crystal Caverns and asked a 50+ character farming the Geonid camp for money if he/she wouldn't mind me joining for exp only. So I guess it was more Leeching than PLing. Awesome experience. Zone is mostly empty nowadays... I remeber the days when I went there with my main and it was not only camped but with a waiting list as well. Much like HHK.
<br />

<br />
My Attack skills were pretty much maxed all along my leveling. Raising Defense was a pain, though. Instrument skill ups are a joke when you can AFK at PoK while singing. In fact, while at it, you can sing Enduring Breath and max your swimming as well at a home town. 
<br />

<br />
Oh, I didn't use a 1hb weapon till like 60. Bought 2 of them and got from 0 to 250 in a couple days at PoV.
<br />

<br />
If you care about skilling up, IMO Best PLer is Shamman. Slow and heals allow for bard tanking. DEX buff will help with offense skills, while AGI will help with Defense skill.
<br />

<br />
If you don't care about anything but experience. Then best PLer is Chanter. A chanter can Charm-PL spirocs for a low level all day long. Slow something, charm it, send it to another mob. Mez the mob when charmed pet about to die. Break charm, spiroc starts to flee away. Bard snare it and chant it down or melee it down. Wash, rinse, repeat. At 46 Chanter can do the same with tier 1 PoP zones. At 55 PoV. At 62 HoH.
<br />

<br />
Mob killing speed &gt; All.
<br />

<br />
Nilufer</span></td>
